The paper deals with video super-resolution reconstruction (SRR) algorithms, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) communities. The proposed algorithm involves optimization using a nonlinear cost function, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of an efficient projection scheme is also a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
